{
  "doc_id": "39144",
  "text": "ABH antigens can be present on key receptors controlling cell proliferation, adhesion, and motility, such as the epidermal growth factor receptor, integrins, cadherins, and CD44 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The expression pattern of these various receptors differs according to the type of cancer, and therefore the role of ABH antigens in the biology of human cancers may also vary. In this regard, it is not clear at present how representative the results described here using a rat experimental model might be. Whatever the case, cellular mechanisms promoting apoptotic cell death are connected with cell proliferation and prevent the accumulation of deleterious mutations and the development of cancer. It is therefore to be expected that elements counteracting apoptotis should favor the survival of cells harboring genetic anomalies that lead to cancer progression [CITATION_4] .",
